pecific narratives through specific forms of media. Their analysis leads them to make the case as to whether each of these societies experienced a cultural trauma as a result of the way in which the war is remembered.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCollective memoryzUnited States. 0aCollective memoryzVietnam. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975. 4aConflict and Peace. 4aContemporary Society. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aSociology and Social History. 4aSouth East Asia. 7aHISTORY / Military / Vietnam War.2bisacsh  aVietnam War, Cultural Trauma, Arenas of Memory, Memorialisation.1 aMadigan, Todd, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRing, Magnus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cprintz978946372308440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048556397?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048556397423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048556397/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGB